Name: SharedTerminology
Description:
The Shared Terminology data mart is a repository containing standard reference information to be leveraged in the EDW. There are many standard code sets, value sets, and mappings that are installed and updated on a regular basis.
The purpose of the content is to provide consistent and up-to-date displays for commonly used code sets. Additionally, the value sets can be used as building blocks for clinical applications and analytics.

A Health Catalyst reference table containing the Clinical Integration Hierarchy (aka Clinical Hierarchy or Care Process Hierarchy).             ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(ORDER BY s1.number) AS DateID
            ,DateRangeStartDate
            ,FiscalStartMonth
         FROM InputCTE
         CROSS JOIN NumberCTE AS s1
                              CROSS JOIN NumberCTE AS s2),

     CalendarCTE
     AS (SELECT
             DateDTS
            ,DateID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(dd,DATEADD(dd,-8,DateRangeStartDate),DateDTS) / 7 AS INT) AS WeekID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(mm,DATEADD(mm,-1,DateRangeStartDate),DateDTS) AS INT) AS MonthID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(qq,DATEADD(qq,-1,DateRangeStartDate),DateDTS) AS INT) AS QuarterID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(mm,DateRangeStartDate,DateDTS) / 6 + 1 AS INT) AS HalfYearID
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS INT) AS YearID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(dd,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 7 AS INT) AS FiscalWeekID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(mm,DATEADD(mm,-1,FiscalStartDate),DateDTS) AS INT) AS FiscalMonthID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(qq,DATEADD(qq,-1,FiscalStartDate),DateDTS) AS INT) AS FiscalQuarterID
            ,CAST(DATEDIFF(mm,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 6 + 1 AS INT) AS FiscalHalfYearID
            ,DATEADD(yy,DATEDIFF(yy,0,DateDTS),0) AS YearStartDTS
            ,DATEADD(yy,DATEDIFF(yy,0,DateDTS) + 1,-1) AS YearEndDTS
            ,DATEADD(yy,DATEDIFF(mm,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 12,FiscalStartDate) AS FiscalYearStartDTS
            ,DATEADD(dd,364,DATEADD(yy,DATEDIFF(mm,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 12,FiscalStartDate)) AS FiscalYearEndDTS
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS INT) AS YearNBR
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(4))+'-Q'+CAST(DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(1)) AS YearQuarterNM
            ,DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) AS QuarterNBR
            ,'Q'+CAST(DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(1)) AS QuarterNM
            ,(DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) + 1) / 2 AS CalendarHalfNBR
            ,'H'+CAST((DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) + 1) / 2 AS VARCHAR(1)) AS CalendarHalfNM
            ,'H'+CAST((DATEPART(qq,DateDTS) + 1) / 2 AS VARCHAR(1))+'-'+CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(4)) AS CalendarHalfYearNM
            ,CAST(CASE
                      WHEN(DATEDIFF(mm,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 6 + 1) % 2 = 1 THEN 1
                      ELSE 2
                  END AS INT) AS FiscalHalfNBR
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+RIGHT('00'+CAST(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(2)),2) AS YearMonthNM
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+CONVERT(CHAR(3),DateDTS,0) AS YearMonthAbbreviatedNM
            ,DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) AS MonthNBR
            ,DATENAME(mm,DateDTS) AS MonthNM
            ,CONVERT(CHAR(3),DateDTS,0) AS MonthAbbreviatedNM
            ,CAST(DATEADD(mm,DATEDIFF(mm,0,DateDTS),0) AS DATETIME) AS MonthStartDTS
            ,CAST(EOMONTH(DateDTS) AS DATETIME) AS MonthEndDTS
            ,CAST(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+RIGHT('00'+CAST(DATEPART(wk,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(2)),2) AS YearWeekNM
            ,DATEPART(wk,DateDTS) AS WeekOfYearNBR
            ,DATEADD(dd,-(DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) - 1),DateDTS) AS WeekStartDTS
            ,DATEADD(dd,7 - DATEPART(dw,DateDTS),DateDTS) AS WeekEndDTS
            ,DATEPART(dy,DateDTS) AS DayOfYearNBR
            ,DATEPART(dd,DateDTS) AS DayOfMonthNBR
            ,DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) AS DayOfWeekNBR
            ,CAST(CASE
                      WHEN DATEPART(Month,DateDTS) >= FiscalStartMonth THEN DATEPART(Year,DateDTS) + 1
                      ELSE DATEPART(Year,DateDTS)
                  END AS INT) AS FiscalYearNBR
            ,CASE
                 WHEN(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) + 13 - FiscalStartMonth) % 12 = 0 THEN 12
                 ELSE(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) + 13 - FiscalStartMonth) % 12
             END AS FiscalMonthNBR  /*Created By Carlos Baldemar*/

            ,FLOOR((CASE
                        WHEN(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) + 13 - FiscalStartMonth) % 12 = 0 THEN 12
                        ELSE(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) + 13 - FiscalStartMonth) % 12
                    END - 1) / 3) + 1 AS FiscalQuarterNBR  /*Created By Carlos Baldemar*/

            ,FLOOR(DATEDIFF(DAY,DATEADD(yy,DATEDIFF(mm,FiscalStartDate,DateDTS) / 12,FiscalStartDate),DATEADD(DAY,-DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) + 1,DateDTS) + 7) / 7) + 1 AS PreFiscalWeekNBR  /*Created By Carlos Baldemar*/

            ,DATENAME(dw,DateDTS) AS WeekdayNM
            ,CASE
                 WHEN DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) IN(7,1) THEN 1
                 ELSE 0
             END AS IsWeekendFLG
            ,CASE
                 WHEN DATEPART(dd,EOMONTH(CONCAT(DATEPART(yy,DateDTS),'0201'))) = 29 THEN 1
                 ELSE 0
             END AS IsLeapYearFLG
            ,CAST(DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(1))+'-'+LEFT(DATENAME(dw,DateDTS),3) AS DayOfWeekNumberAbbreviatedNM
            ,LEFT(DATENAME(dw,DateDTS),3) AS DayOfWeekAbbreviatedNM
            ,CASE
                 WHEN DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) IN(7,1) THEN 'WeekEnd'
                 ELSE 'WeekDay'
             END AS DayTypeDSC
            ,CAST(DATEPART(mm,DateDTS) AS VARCHAR(2))+'-'+CONVERT(CHAR(3),DateDTS,0) AS MonthNumberAbbreviatedNM
         FROM DateRangeCTE
         CROSS JOIN FiscalStartDateCTE),

     WeekDayOfMonthCTE
     AS (SELECT
             DateDTS
            ,CAST(ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY YearMonthNM ORDER BY DateDTS) AS INT) AS WeekDayOfMonthNBR
         FROM CalendarCTE AS DD
         WHERE DATEPART(dw,DateDTS) NOT IN(1,7)),

     DateCTE
     AS (SELECT
             DD.DateDTS
            ,DD.DateID
            ,DD.WeekID
            ,DD.MonthID
            ,DD.QuarterID
            ,DD.HalfYearID
            ,DD.YearID
            ,DD.FiscalWeekID
            ,DD.FiscalMonthID
            ,DD.FiscalQuarterID
            ,DD.FiscalHalfYearID
            ,DD.YearStartDTS
            ,DD.YearEndDTS
            ,DD.FiscalYearStartDTS
            ,DD.FiscalYearEndDTS
            ,DD.YearNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.YearNBR AS VARCHAR)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.MonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2) AS INT) AS YearMonthNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.YearNBR AS VARCHAR)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.MonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.DayOfMonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2) AS INT) AS YearMonthDayNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.YearNBR AS VARCHAR) + CAST(DD.QuarterNBR AS VARCHAR) AS INT) AS YearQuarterNBR
            ,DD.YearQuarterNM
            ,DD.QuarterNBR
            ,DD.QuarterNM
            ,DD.CalendarHalfNBR
            ,DD.CalendarHalfNM
            ,DD.CalendarHalfYearNM
            ,DD.FiscalHalfNBR
            ,'H'+CAST(DD.FiscalHalfNBR AS VARCHAR(1)) AS FiscalHalfNM
            ,'H'+CAST(DD.FiscalHalfNBR AS VARCHAR(1))+'-'+CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR(4)) AS FiscalHalfYearNM
            ,DD.YearMonthNM
            ,DD.YearMonthAbbreviatedNM
            ,DD.MonthNBR
            ,DD.MonthNM
            ,DD.MonthAbbreviatedNM
            ,DD.MonthStartDTS
            ,DD.MonthEndDTS
            ,DD.YearWeekNM
            ,DD.WeekOfYearNBR
            ,DD.WeekStartDTS
            ,DD.WeekEndDTS
            ,DD.DayOfYearNBR
            ,DD.DayOfMonthNBR
            ,DD.DayOfWeekNBR
            ,DD.FiscalYearNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.FiscalMonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2) AS INT) AS FiscalYearMonthNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.FiscalMonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2)+RIGHT('0'+CAST(DD.DayOfMonthNBR AS VARCHAR),2) AS INT) AS FiscalYearMonthDayNBR
            ,CAST(CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR) + CAST(DD.FiscalQuarterNBR AS VARCHAR) AS INT) AS FiscalYearQuarterNBR
            ,DD.FiscalQuarterNBR
            ,DD.FiscalMonthNBR
            ,CASE
                 WHEN DATEPART(dw,DD.FiscalYearStartDTS) = 1 THEN DD.PreFiscalWeekNBR - 1
                 ELSE DD.PreFiscalWeekNBR
             END AS FiscalWeekNBR
            ,CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR(4))+'-Q'+CAST(DD.FiscalQuarterNBR AS VARCHAR(1)) AS FiscalYearQuarterNM
            ,CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+CAST(DD.FiscalMonthNBR AS VARCHAR(2)) AS FiscalYearMonthNM
            ,CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+CAST(DD.FiscalMonthNBR AS VARCHAR(2))+'('+CAST(DD.MonthAbbreviatedNM AS VARCHAR(3))+')' AS FiscalYearMonthAbbreviatedNM
            ,CAST(DD.FiscalYearNBR AS VARCHAR(4))+'-'+CAST(CASE
                                                               WHEN DATEPART(dw,DD.FiscalYearStartDTS) = 1 THEN DD.PreFiscalWeekNBR - 1
                                                               ELSE DD.PreFiscalWeekNBR
                                                           END AS VARCHAR(2)) AS FiscalYearWeekNM
            ,DD.WeekdayNM
            ,WD.WeekDayOfMonthNBR
            ,DD.IsWeekendFLG
            ,DD.IsLeapYearFLG
            ,CAST(MAX(WD.WeekDayOfMonthNBR) OVER(PARTITION BY DD.YearMonthNM) AS INT) AS MonthTotalWorkDayCNT
            ,DD.DayOfWeekNumberAbbreviatedNM
            ,DD.DayOfWeekAbbreviatedNM
            ,DD.DayTypeDSC
            ,DD.MonthNumberAbbreviatedNM
            ,CASE
                /* New Years Day*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 1
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 1
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR BETWEEN 2 AND 6 THEN 'New Year''s Day' /* Falls on Weekday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 1
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 2
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'New Year''s Day' /* Falls on Sunday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 12
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 31
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 6 THEN 'New Year''s Day' /* Falls on Saturday Martin Luther King Day (3rd Monday of January)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 1
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 15 AND 21
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Martin Luther King Day'
                /* Presidents Day (3rd Monday of February)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 2
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 15 AND 21
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'President''s Day'
                /* Memorial Day (Last Monday of May)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 5
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 25 AND 31
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Memorial Day'
                /* Independence Day*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 7
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 4
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR BETWEEN 2 AND 6 THEN 'Independence Day' /* Falls on Weekday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 7
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 5
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Independence Day' /* Falls on Sunday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 7
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 3
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 6 THEN 'Independence Day' /* Falls on Saturday Labor Day (1st Monday of September)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 9
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 1 AND 7
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Labor Day'
                /* Columbus Day (2nd Monday of October)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 10
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 8 AND 14
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Columbus Day'
                /* Veterans Day (October 11th)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 11
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 11
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR BETWEEN 2 AND 6 THEN 'Veteran''s Day' /* Falls on Weekday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 11
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 12
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Veteran''s Day' /* Falls on Sunday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 11
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 10
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 6 THEN 'Veteran''s Day' /* Falls on Saturday Thanksgiving Day (4th Thursday of November)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 11
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR BETWEEN 22 AND 28
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 5 THEN 'Thanksgiving Day'
                /* Christmas Day (December 25th)*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 12
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 25
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR BETWEEN 2 AND 6 THEN 'Christmas Day' /* Falls on Weekday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 12
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 26
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 2 THEN 'Christmas Day' /* Falls on Sunday*/
                 WHEN DD.MonthNBR = 12
                      AND DD.DayOfMonthNBR = 24
                      AND DD.DayOfWeekNBR = 6 THEN 'Christmas Day' /* Falls on Saturday*/
             END AS HolidayDSC
         FROM CalendarCTE AS DD
         LEFT JOIN WeekDayOfMonthCTE AS WD
            ON DD.DateDTS = WD.DateDTS)

SELECT

   ,CASE
        WHEN HolidayDSC IS NOT NULL THEN 'Federal'
        ELSE NULL
    END AS HolidayTypeDSC
   ,CASE
